Meta=E2=80=99s Quest 3 Announcement
---------------------------

From Bloomberg ( https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-06-01/meta-an=
nounces-500-quest-3-headset-just-ahead-of-apple-launch ) :

Meta Platforms Inc.=C2=A0announced the latest version of its Quest mixed-re=
ality headset, a lower-cost alternative to the long-awaited device that=C2=
=A0Apple Inc.=C2=A0is expected to unveil in a few days. The new Meta Quest =
3 will cost $500 and ship in the fall, the company said in a blog post ( ht=
tps://about.fb.com/news/2023/06/meta-quest-3-coming-this-fall/ ) Thursday. =
Meta, which also owns Facebook and Instagram, said it will continue to sell=
 the Quest 2 model at a lower price, $300, to help =E2=80=9Ceven more peopl=
e access the magic of VR.=E2=80=9D

I=E2=80=99ve already talked about this announcement on Dithering ( https://=
dithering.fm/ ) and Sharp Tech, so I don=E2=80=99t want to dwell on this, b=
ut this pre-announcement is incredibly weak. The upside, as far as I can de=
termine, is that every article this week about Apple=E2=80=99s headset is g=
oing to mention the Quest 3. Given that Apple drives more press coverage th=
an any other company, by far, I can see the allure.

The downside is, well, looking desperate for attention: obviously Meta feel=
s neither the Quest 2 nor the Quest Pro are going to compare favorably to A=
pple=E2=80=99s headset (the resolution issues I noted above loom large here=
), but instead of biding their time, seeing what Apple actually releases, a=
nd crafting a message to counter that, Meta shot their shot with the Quest =
3 news. Is anyone going to care when this announcement comes in September? =
A new product is going to be old news!

All this does is reinforce my questions about why exactly Meta is making a =
headset at all. Yes, I get that Apple is anything but a reliable partner, a=
nd being a horizontal services company in a world where you don=E2=80=99t o=
wn a platform is a difficult place to be. It doesn=E2=80=99t follow, though=
, that becoming a vertical platform company that =E2=80=94 as evidenced by =
this announcement =1F=E2=80=94 places you in opposition to a platform you o=
ught to be present on is the solution!

The irony of all of this is that the best possible version of Apple=E2=80=
=99s announcement would actually include Meta: presence is a real thing, an=
d Meta is working to build a social world in VR; it would be very compellin=
g to see Zuckerberg on stage demoing the application they built for Apple=
=E2=80=99s headset. This is clearly the way, but like Uber and Waymo ( http=
s://stratechery.com/2023/microns-china-ban-neeva-gives-up-on-search-uber-an=
d-waymo-finally/?access_token=3DeyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6InN0cmF0ZWNoZXJ=
